Package gw.api.inboundfile

Class InboundRecordReader

java.lang.Object
gw.api.inboundfile.InboundRecordReader
All Implemented Interfaces:
AutoCloseable
Direct Known Subclasses:
JsonInboundRecordReader, YamlInboundRecordReader, YamlMultiDocTextRecordReader
public abstract class InboundRecordReader extends Object implements AutoCloseable
Base class for a reader returned by InboundFileHandler.createReader(InboundFile, InputStream, AtomicInteger) Typically the implementation of the readRecord is just embedded so that the parameters of the call are present. Instances of this class should be considered NOT thread-safe. They should also be assumed to have resources, so they should be closed.

  • Method Details

    • readRecord

      public abstract InboundRecord readRecord(Bundle bundle) throws Exception
      This method returns the next record. This should be a newly record created in supplied bundle. Implementer note -- this needs to be implemented. There are helper methods: createInboundRecord(Bundle, InboundRecordStatus, String, Integer) and addInboundSubRecord(InboundRecord, String, Integer) to help you construct that record. For example BaseInboundFileHandler could implement its createReader: 
      
   final AtomicBoolean done = new AtomicBoolean();
   return new InboundRecordReader(_config, inboundFileBean) {
     public InboundRecord readRecord(Bundle bundle) throws IOException {
       if (!done.get()) {
         done.set(true);
         return createInboundRecord(bundle, InboundRecordStatus.TC_PENDING, StreamUtil.toString(StreamUtil.getContent(inputStream)), 0);
       }
       return null;
      }
     };
      Parameters:
      bundle - the bundle to create new beans in
      Returns:
      a new InboundRecord in the current bundle (note that it will have its chunk set after it's returned and before it's committed)
      Throws:
      Exception - if there are processing errors
